18 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Definitions. As used in this chapter, the following definitions apply:
19 (1) "FDA" means the United States food and drug administration.
20 (2) "Importer" means a person or entity in a state or territory of the United States to whom vapor
21 products that are manufactured outside the United States are shipped, delivered, or consigned for resale.
22 (3) "Retailer" means a person, other than a wholesaler, who is licensed by the department of
23 revenue and who is engaged in the business of selling vapor products to the ultimate consumer.
24 (4) "Timely filed premarket tobacco product application" means an application pursuant to 21
25 U.S.C. 387j for a vapor product containing nicotine derived from tobacco marketed in the United States as of
26 August 8, 2016, that was submitted to the United States food and drug administration on or before September
27 9, 2020, and accepted for filing.
28 (5) "Units sold" means the number of individual vapor products containing nicotine sold in the state
